card.city

Enum AnkhMorporkArea

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AnkhMorporkArea>
      • card.city.AnkhMorporkArea
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Card, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<AnkhMorporkArea>

    public enum AnkhMorporkArea
extends java.lang.Enum<AnkhMorporkArea>
implements Card
    An enumeration of all the areas available in the game. Each area is uniquely identified by a number (which is visible on the physical game board).
    Note that this area implements the Card marker interface, because it serves as the enumeration of all the City Area cards in the game while CityAreaCard actually bears the state of the card (played or not, playable more than once etc.).
    Version:
    2.0
    Author:
    Team 10 - SOEN6441
